SIMPLE: putrescent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Putrescent
<hw>Pu*tres"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>putrescens</ets>, p. pr.of <ets>putrescere</ets> to grow rotten, v.
incho. fr. <ets>putrere</ets> to be rotten. See <er>Putrid</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Becoming putrid or rotten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Externally powerful, although <qex>putrescent</qex> at the
core.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the process of putrefaction;
<as>as, a <ex>putrescent</ex> smell</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Putrescible</ent>⟦br⟧
